{
  "texts": [
    "In so doing, they strengthen youth curiosity and appreciation for the salience of building innovative tools with AI/ML.",
    "In sum, by working across a collection of contexts, we are reminded how these different spaces can engage youth in distinct learning with and through AI/ML, in part, as facilitated through the unique set of mentors and collaborators that occupy each space.",
    "Building your own generative language model: High school students' engagement with data practices and ethical considerations when designing babyGPTs Luis Morales-Navarro, Daniel J. Noh, Yasmin B. Kafai As generative language models (GLMs) have gained popularity, youth are increasingly using them in their everyday lives.",
    "However, most research has centered on supporting youth as users of GLM-powered systems (e.g., Solyst et al., 2024).",
    "At the same time, research on how youth engage with the design of ML models has mostly centered on classification tasks with little attention given to generative tasks."
  ]
}